This is the generic conversation tree for henchmen in X0. 

IMPORTANT RULES:
- do not add any new items to the top-level tree unless you're sure you know what you're doing;

- only change RED or BLUE dialogue entries. The grey ones are links to other sections. Be careful to add new links (use copy & paste-as-link on the right-mouse-button menu) if you change options in a dialogue with linked entries;

- always check the 'Text Appears When' and 'Actions Taken' tabs before mucking with the existing lines. In the script preview window you should be able to see the comment describing what each script does so you can understand the effects of making changes;

- remember that any time you have more than one possible '[OWNER]' line at a given level of dialogue, they should all have conditions, and those conditions should be exhaustive (meaning that they should cover the full range of possibilities) or you should have a default line that will serve as the catch-all. 

- one significant change: we don't need to restrict henchmen to only be hired by one person ever. IE, if you fire a henchman, another player in the same game can hire them instead. If they fire the henchman, you can then rehire them. Keep this in mind for conversation writing.

Each henchman has three inital greetings which are their first greeting to the player in each act. The conversation needs to work regardless of whether the player is starting with this act or has come to it from a previous act. 
There are also alternative first greetings for acts 2 & 3 in case you want to write one where the player has the personal item already; if you DO NOT want alternative ones, DELETE THOSE LINES.

They each have three "hello again" greetings, one for each module. These can assume that the player has already met the henchman and has that info, so can be much shorter. 

The interjections are on the top-level; the advice sections are under the 'I'm working for you' tree.
